Sec. 161.0416. EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT. (a) The commission may
prepare and plan for, respond to, and aid in the recovery from
disaster events that may affect livestock, exotic livestock, domestic
fowl, or exotic fowl, including disease outbreaks, hurricanes,
floods, tornadoes, wildfires, and acts of terrorism.
(b) The commission may assist with local emergency management
planning. This subsection may not be construed to affect the
commission's responsibility under any other law, including Chapter
418, Government Code, or any responsibility delegated to the
commission by an emergency management authority of this state.
Added by Acts 2007, 80th Leg., R.S., Ch. 1242 (H.B. 2543), Sec. 12,
eff. September 1, 2007.

